{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "apex", "namespace": "apex", "internal": "rig::SplineInterpolateTransforms", "version": "", "tags": "apex", "since": "20.0"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["rig::SplineInterpolateTransforms"], "extent": [124, 161]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates and samples a spline."], "extent": [161, 201]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates a spline from a number of input control matrices. The position of the control matrices defines the shape of the generated spline, while the upper 3\u00d73 transform of the control matrices defines the framing of the spline. The generated spline is then resampled a variable number of times to produce output transforms that are made available on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["resampled"]}, " subport. Additional twists can be applied to the output transforms via the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["twists"]}, " port."], "extent": [201, 663]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [663, 669], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The output transforms are oriented such that their -Z axis points toward the next sample, and their +Y axis matches as closely as possible to the interpolated +Y axis of the control matrices. This behavior is the source of some instability, so it is recommended that ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransforms", "type": "link", "text": ["rig::SplineInterpolateTransforms::2.0"], "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransforms.html"}, " be used, which corrects this instability and adds additional flexibility for the user to choose the tangent direction that points toward the next sample."], "extent": [669, 1178]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Internally, the spline generated from the control matrices is a bezier curve of the specified ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["order"]}, ". This means that the number of control matrices must satisfy the equation, ", {"type": "code", "text": ["<number_of_cvs> % (order-1) == 1"]}, ". This constraint may be lifted in a future version of Houdini, but as a workaround, users can generate a NURBS curve with the desired number of control points (with a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["transform"]}, " point attribute), and use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms", "type": "link", "text": ["rig::SampleSplineTransforms"], "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms.html"}, " to sample the control curve."], "extent": [1178, 1695]}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1695, 1703], "body": [{"type": "inputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["cvs"], "role": "item", "extent": [1703, 1712], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The control matrices used to generate and frame a control spline. The number of control matrices must satisfy the equation, ", {"type": "code", "text": ["<number_of_cvs> % (order-1) == 1"]}, "."], "extent": [1744, 1909]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "VariadicArg<Matrix4>"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["twists"], "role": "item", "extent": [1909, 1920], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Additional twists (in radians) to add to the output transforms. There does NOT have to be a twist value per CV. Adding values 0 and 2*M_PI twists the output transforms a full rotation about the transforms' Z axes. Additional twist values are interpolated linearly between the values across the length of the spline."], "extent": [1950, 2271]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "VariadicArg<Float>"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["order"], "role": "item", "extent": [2271, 2281], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The order of the generated spline curve."], "extent": [2296, 2342]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["smooth"], "role": "item", "extent": [2342, 2352], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If set to True, adds smoothstep smoothing to the output transforms. The default value is False."], "extent": [2368, 2469]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Bool"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2469, 2478], "body": [{"type": "outputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "outputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["resampled"], "role": "item", "extent": [2478, 2492], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The resampled transforms. The number of connections to this port controls the number of resampled points on the generated spline."], "extent": [2524, 2659]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "VariadicArg<Matrix4>"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2659, 2668], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSpline", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSpline.html"}], "extent": [2668, 2701]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSplineFromArray", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSplineFromArray.html"}], "extent": [2701, 2743]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms.html"}], "extent": [2743, 2785]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransformsToArray", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransformsToArray.html"}], "extent": [2785, 2834]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransformsToArray", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransformsToArray.html"}], "extent": [2834, 2887]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["rig::SplineInterpolateTransforms"], "summary": ["Generates and samples a spline."]}